  "text": "The Chromium renderer process sandbox implementation spans multiple files across different platforms:\n\n**1. Linux Seccomp-BPF Base Policy (sandbox/linux/)**:\nThe base policy for Linux sandboxing is implemented in `sandbox/linux/seccomp-bpf-helpers/baseline_policy.h`, which defines the `BaselinePolicy` class that extends the `bpf_dsl::Policy` interface (defined in `sandbox/linux/bpf_dsl/policy.h`). The `BaselinePolicy` class implements the `EvaluateSyscall()` method to define seccomp-BPF rules that control which system calls are allowed in the renderer process sandbox. This is the foundational policy used for all Linux-based sandboxing.\n\n**2. Windows Sandbox Policy Configuration (sandbox/win/src/)**:\nThe Windows sandbox policy is defined in `sandbox/win/src/sandbox_policy.h`, which contains two key classes: `TargetConfig` and `TargetPolicy`. `TargetConfig` (lines 58-258) manages the base configuration for target processes, including methods like `SetTokenLevel()` and `SetJobLevel()` to configure security levels. `TargetPolicy` (lines 263-286) is the abstract interface that wraps the config and provides handle sharing functionality. These classes are instantiated in `sandbox/win/src/sandbox.h` through `BrokerServices::CreatePolicy()`.\n\n**3. Sandbox Type Enumeration and Mappings (sandbox/policy/)**:\nThe `SandboxType` enum is defined in `sandbox/policy/mojom/sandbox.mojom` as `enum Sandbox`, which includes types like `kRenderer`, `kGpu`, `kUtility`, `kService`, etc. The implementation of sandbox type management functions is in `sandbox/policy/sandbox_type.h` and `sandbox/policy/sandbox_type.cc`, which includes key functions like `IsUnsandboxedSandboxType()`, `SetCommandLineFlagsForSandboxType()`, and `SandboxTypeFromCommandLine()`. These map sandbox types to their specific security configurations.\n\n**4. Renderer Process Sandbox Configuration (content/browser/)**:\nThe renderer process specifically is configured through `content/browser/renderer_host/renderer_sandboxed_process_launcher_delegate.h`, which defines the `RendererSandboxedProcessLauncherDelegate` class. This class overrides `GetSandboxType()` to return `sandbox::mojom::Sandbox::kRenderer`. On Windows, the `RendererSandboxedProcessLauncherDelegateWin` subclass (lines 37-57) implements `InitializeConfig(sandbox::TargetConfig* config)` to apply renderer-specific security policies including token levels, mitigation flags, and AppContainer configuration. The implementation is in `renderer_sandboxed_process_launcher_delegate.cc`.\n\nThese components work together to enforce a layered sandbox architecture: the enumeration defines available sandbox types, policy/sandbox_type.cc maps these types to security configurations, TargetPolicy/TargetConfig implement platform-specific restrictions, and the renderer delegate applies these configurations when launching renderer processes."
}

